The directorate of criminal investigations now says it recovered 5.7 million shillings from a woman alleged to have been on the way to present the money to judges Said Chitembwe and Aggrey Muchelule. In an affidavit sworn by one felix karisa, dci detectives are believed to have been tipped off that a broker was on the way to present one of the judges with 7 million shillings at his residence for a favorable ruling but the plan changed and was instead told to take the money to the judge&rsquo;s chamber at the Milimani law courts.
